[SN]TITLE[SN]
Eoghan O'Connell: Celtic defender joins Walsall on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League One club Walsall have signed Celtic centre-back Eoghan O'Connell on loan until the end of the season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 21-year-old Republic of Ireland Under-21 international has played seven games for the Scottish champions this season, including a Champions League group game against Barcelona.
"We've had to fight off competition from clubs in England and the SPFL," Saddlers boss Jon Whitney said.
Left-back Scott Laird has also extended his loan until the end of the season.
The 28-year-old spent the first half of the campaign on loan from Scunthorpe, scoring three goals in 22 games.
